    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - STOPMASTER WEDGE TYPE BRAKE - OPERATION - PLUNGER AND SHOE POSITION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="2">
        <title>PLUNGER AND SHOE POSITION</title>
        <para>On double-actuated brakes (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0401315">Figure 15</hotlnk>and
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0401316">Figure 16</hotlnk>), the anchor (solid) plungers should be positioned at the
            trailing end of each shoe (where they will absorb the brake torque during forward wheel rotation). This will
            position the adjustable plungers at the leading end of the shoes. Also note that the shoe web is
            unsymmetrical. The long-radius end should be engaged with the adjustable plungers.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0401315" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0401315.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. Left Hand Brake</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WHEEL ROTATION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LONG RADIUS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ADJUSTABLE PLUNGER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. ANCHOR PLUNGER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f0401316" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/G0401316.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 16. Right Hand Brake</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. WHEEL ROTATION</callout1>
                <callout1>2. LONG RADIUS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ADJUSTABLE PLUNGER</callout1>
                <callout1>4. ANCHOR PLUNGER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
